 controversies; the effect on households, social systems and economics; the care of the sick and the search for remedies and vaccines; and the impact of antiretroviral treatments. This book uses medical, anthropological and eye-witness sources but assumes no prior knowledge. Professor Iliffe has forty years experience of teaching in Africa and Britain. His books on modern African history are renowned. North America: Ohio U Press; South Africa: Double Storey/Juta  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAIDS (Disease)zAfricaxHistory. 4aAfrican Studies. 7aHISTORY / Africa / General.2bisacsh  aAfrican AIDS epidemic.  aAfrican continent.  aNGOs.  aantiretroviral treatments.  acare of the sick.  aeconomic impact.  aepidemic progress.  agovernment responses.  ahistory.  amoral controversies.  aremedies.  asocial impact.  avaccines.  avirus.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781782049906?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782049906423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782049906/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles